f(x)=\sin(2x)+2\sin(x)
\sin^2 x + \cos^2x = 1
f(x) = \sin 2x + 2 \sin x = 2 \sin x ( 1 + \cos x )
\sin x \geq 0, \cos x \geq 0
[f(x)]^2 = 4 \sin^2 x ( 1 + \cos x)^2 = 4 (1-\cos^2x ) ( 1 + \cos x)^2 = 4 ( 1 - \cos x ) ( 1 + \cos x)^3 
 3(1-\cos x) , (1 + \cos x), (1 + \cos x), (1 + \cos x)
 \sqrt[4]{3 ( 1 - \cos x ) ( 1 + \cos x)^3} \leq \frac{ 6}{4}
 ( 1 - \cos x ) ( 1 + \cos x)^3 \leq \frac{27}{16}
 [f(x)]^2 \leq \frac{27}{4}
f(x) \leq \frac{3 \sqrt{3} } {2} 
3(1-\cos x) = 1 + \cos x
\cos x = \frac{1}{2}
\sin x,\cos x>0 \implies 0\le x\le \frac\pi2
\implies 0\le 2x\le \pi\implies0\le \pi-2x\le \pi
x=x=\pi-2x
x=\frac\pi3
=\sin(\pi-2x)+\sin x+\sin x\le 3\sin\frac{(\pi-2x+x+x)}3=3\sin\frac{\pi}3=\frac{3\sqrt3}2
